Implemented the minimal fix in `src/main.c`.

What changed:
- `--` now stops option parsing even when it appears before the jq program.
- The next argument after `--` is treated as the jq program if no program has been seen yet.
- A bare trailing `--` still errors instead of falling through to the implicit `.` program behavior.

Verified with:
- `make -j2`
- `./jq --null-input --args -- '$ARGS' foo bar baz --zorch`
- Confirmed existing behavior remains: `./jq --null-input --args '$ARGS' foo bar baz --zorch` still reports unknown option.
- Confirmed bare `./jq -n --` still exits with usage/error.
